# Quarto build artifacts
_book/
_site/
.quarto/
_freeze/              # Quarto's cache of executed code chunks (regenerated on render)
*_files/
*_cache/
**/*.quarto_ipynb

# LaTeX intermediates (if keep-tex produced them)
*.aux
*.log
*.out
*.bbl
*.blg
*.synctex.gz

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Editor
.vscode/
.idea/

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Privacy + operational exclusions (do NOT publish to GitHub)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

# Private mirrors of Drive docs (in-progress drafts, meeting notes, proposals)
# These are meant as LOCAL working copies only — the Drive originals are the
# source of truth and the repo should never leak pre-publication prose.
**/drafts/from-drive/

# Nightly-generated PowerPoint recaps would bloat git history quickly.
# The reveal.js .qmd presentations ARE committed (they're text and render to
# HTML via Quarto) — only the binary .pptx versions are excluded.
**/presentations/*.pptx
**/presentations/daily/*.pptx

# Rendered slideshow HTML — regenerated by Quarto, not versioned.
**/presentations/*.html

# Rendered chapter HTML (built by `quarto render`, should not be committed).
chapter*.html

# Quarto sometimes emits a single-file LaTeX artifact at repo root when PDF
# rendering fails mid-way. Always a build artifact, never hand-written.
/*.tex

# Stray files accidentally created by shell typos (e.g. `cat > -`).
/-

# Figure PDFs — we keep only PNGs in the repo (they render in HTML and
# embed fine in Quarto's PDF output). Analysis scripts may still emit PDFs
# locally, but sync_figures.sh ignores them. This keeps the repo ~200 MB
# lighter than the prior state.
chapter-*/figures/*.pdf

# QA artifacts from local `quarto preview` or PPT-to-image renders.
**/presentations/daily/slide-*.jpg
**/presentations/daily/slide-*.png
**/presentations/daily/*.pdf

# Operational session output — valuable locally but often contains working
# notes, session IDs, and ideas not ready for public review.
**/daily-summaries/

# Large data — never commit raw scientific datasets to GitHub.
# Use Zenodo, Google Drive, or Box for data releases.
**/data/raw/
**/data/processed/
**/data/interim/
*.nc
*.nc4
*.netcdf
*.h5
*.hdf5
*.parquet

# Communication feedback inbox — contains free-form gripes / preferences
# that aren't polished for public consumption.
**/communication-feedback.md
**/communication-feedback-archive.md

# Memory consolidation log — internal operational audit trail.
**/memory-consolidation-log.md

/.quarto/
